Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuritama Episode 5
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.73,0:01:36.70,Ep_Title,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,530)}Discouraged Jerking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.70,0:01:34.59,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Summer vacation started.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:36.82,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.36,0:01:39.28,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you'd want one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.87,0:01:40.81,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.97,0:01:45.29,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just looking at them \Nmade me want my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:49.52,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna buy your own pole, Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:51.36,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I figured we shouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:53.95,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,borrowing poles \Nfrom Misaki-san forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.95,0:01:58.77,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. Misaki's nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:02.03,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she's bothered by that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:05.72,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess you would want your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.72,0:02:06.54,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.20,0:02:09.69,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll get one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.16,0:02:13.02,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I was like that once, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:16.39,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really get into fishing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.39,0:02:19.08,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,until I bought my own gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:21.34,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But they're pretty expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.32,0:02:23.70,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's actually a wide range,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:25.78,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you're going to buy one,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.78,0:02:28.08,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you might as well get something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.83,0:02:30.25,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.24,0:02:34.66,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.66,0:02:35.32,Advert2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're waiting for your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.66,0:02:35.32,Advert3,,0000,0000,0000,,smile
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.32,0:02:38.53,Advert,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}}Help Wanted!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.29,0:02:41.59,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.59,0:02:43.08,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.04,0:02:45.76,Tsuritama_Main,STORE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.78,0:02:50.13,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just go see what they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.14,0:02:56.23,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the captain today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:03:00.26,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's not here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.26,0:03:01.72,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:04.49,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start with rods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:07.62,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for a rod, I'd \Nrecommend one of these over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:09.40,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,How about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.40,0:03:12.46,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no paint coating, \Nso it's pretty light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:14.63,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,They call it unsanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.14,0:03:21.29,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:23.80,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:26.94,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Lunamis S900ML.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:29.64,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Not a bad choice for an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:34.48,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The Lunamis is made primarily \Nfor catching sea bass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:36.98,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a middle-grade rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.37,0:03:39.13,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The amazing thing about this rod is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.75,0:03:39.13,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Try swinging it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:40.32,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:41.98,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}compared to a top-grade rod,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.98,0:03:44.17,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}it performs almost exactly the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:46.37,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's so light. This thing's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:45.92,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}With the surprising power \Nand feel of a Spiral X
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:48.49,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}and Hyperpower X along with \NShinoma's unique construction,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.37,0:03:47.64,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:50.00,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, hold the rod like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:53.79,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}it's got a light and tangle-proof chitin frame K-guide,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.46,0:03:53.74,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to tell \Nthe difference in rigidity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.74,0:03:56.72,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and flexibility compared to \Nthe rod you've been using.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.79,0:03:56.35,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}as well as a lightweight yet strong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.35,0:03:58.77,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sea Eye Four-based reel seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.72,0:03:59.30,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. This is different!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:03.87,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,At 37,500 yen, I think it's a steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.87,0:04:07.39,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,And if you're buying that \Nrod, I recommend this reel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.39,0:04:10.62,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Twin Power C3000HG.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.62,0:04:12.64,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I prefer a Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:17.12,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,This reel's got a reasonable price \Nconsidering its high specs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.12,0:04:20.27,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If the Stella is every fisherman's \Ntrue love or princess,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:23.09,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,this would be the schoolyard's Madonna.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:27.14,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, high school \Nkids like you can afford it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:29.86,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:32.23,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, you seem happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:33.60,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:42.03,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,A hundred thousand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.03,0:04:46.82,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. A Rod and reel, \Nplus lures, fishing wear,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:49.37,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and everything else comes \Nout to around that price.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:51.89,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you're really serious about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:54.17,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll end up spending about that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.17,0:04:57.10,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have that much money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:04:59.69,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's hot out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:01.03,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:01.03,Tsuritama_Overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:02.03,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:06.65,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Natsuki. It's so hot \Nyou could melt, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.65,0:05:09.57,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm melting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.57,0:05:11.99,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Haru, is it hot on your planet, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.99,0:05:14.12,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's super cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.81,0:05:16.12,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He knows about Haru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:18.43,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous, you jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.43,0:05:20.40,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that, Misaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.40,0:05:21.61,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it sound great?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:25.36,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's the perfect place \Nfor a summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:27.69,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Indian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.69,0:05:30.94,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Take off your turban when \Nyou're in the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.94,0:05:32.85,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's making me hot just looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:34.01,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.87,0:05:37.30,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, boy, catch anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:39.84,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki-san, the usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:42.35,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Hot tea, coming right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.13,0:05:48.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:49.72,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.22,0:05:53.31,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's like my older brother. \NHe's a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:55.62,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Ayumi-chan's a great guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.16,0:05:59.85,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't work in a \Nstore, you could probably fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.85,0:06:01.48,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.48,0:06:05.25,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, we don't make \Nany money by fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.25,0:06:07.69,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:09.95,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.95,0:06:11.43,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.71,0:06:15.10,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you let the three \Nof us work this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:18.09,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:20.37,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This summer vacation, I was hoping
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.37,0:06:23.98,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd let the three of us \Nwork on your fishing boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:27.70,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Work on a fishing boat? You can do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.84,0:06:31.91,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's staring me down!\NWhat is this, an interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.66,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What am I gonna do? Should I smile?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:37.12,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:42.29,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's serious about fishing and \Ndesperately wants his own gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.93,0:06:45.68,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.91,0:06:50.72,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, you pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:51.89,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:55.19,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,We pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.19,0:06:56.88,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:58.08,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:07:00.20,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You start tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.20,0:07:01.55,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.64,0:07:04.11,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.03,0:07:08.53,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:12.49,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:16.95,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Three days on my boat and you'll \Nbe a real man of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:20.19,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,A man of the sea? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:21.80,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.80,0:07:23.46,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,We knew we could count on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.84,0:07:26.26,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:30.47,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.47,0:07:33.23,Tsuritama_Overlap,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The god of love must \Nbe smiling down on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.87,0:07:32.75,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This is great, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.23,0:07:35.10,Tsuritama_Overlap,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Thank you, Benten-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.96,0:07:38.10,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,A job?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.34,0:07:41.57,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you do work and get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:45.68,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I know that, but will it \Nmake him better at fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:49.69,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,It's a boat. He'll fish \Nall day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:52.86,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as long as Yuki \Ngets better at fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:55.16,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:07:58.75,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Koko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:08:01.49,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was just feeling a little \Ndried out, so it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:06.03,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But don't go too far out, Nii-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.05,0:08:09.19,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If he's out there, you'll be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.19,0:08:10.13,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.59,0:08:12.19,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.61,0:08:16.49,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they just wanted to fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.83,0:08:18.99,TVScreen,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Top Secret
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:23.60,Tsuritama_Overlap,HIYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Bermuda Syndrome refers \Nto the strange events
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:26.53,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}occurring in the triangular \Nregion of the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.53,0:08:28.88,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}between Florida, Puerto Rico, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.85,0:08:30.24,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:33.00,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Bermuda Islands known \Nas the Bermuda Triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:32.27,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I must go with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:38.12,Tsuritama_Overlap,HIYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Marine vessels and aircrafts \Ndisappear without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:40.87,Tsuritama_Overlap,HIYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}In the moments before they disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.25,0:08:41.60,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,No. This is my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:43.75,Tsuritama_Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}their compasses and other \Ninstruments behave strangely...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:46.61,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.61,0:08:48.82,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.82,0:08:51.73,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that summer sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.73,0:08:54.13,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a perfect day for mahi-mahi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:56.59,Tsuritama_Main,BOAT,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"Seishunmaru"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.59,0:08:59.56,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna catch some mahi-mahi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:00.98,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.58,0:09:04.19,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mahi-mahi are huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.07,0:09:07.49,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are almost two meters long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.49,0:09:08.71,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That big?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:12.01,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Catching them isn't that hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:15.94,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're well known for their violent strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:17.24,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.75,0:09:19.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,They're pretty, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:23.04,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,When they get excited, \Ntheir colors change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:26.33,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I hope I catch one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.33,0:09:27.98,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:33.53,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Fishing, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:39.05,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to fishing with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:49.02,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Yuki. The ocean's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:52.26,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It really is. I'm glad I came.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:00.38,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Do boats always rock this much?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.38,0:10:02.50,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, Haru, get the nets!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.50,0:10:03.53,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.79,0:10:06.86,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Natsuki so calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.86,0:10:12.46,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Nets, nets, nets, nets, nets!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.98,0:10:11.71,Tsuritama_Italic_Overlap,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I should go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.92,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Nets, nets, nets, nets, nets!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.92,0:10:15.84,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:23.18,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ten out of ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.18,0:10:25.77,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.44,0:10:32.61,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:43.38,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, no fair. You're fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.38,0:10:45.85,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm instructing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.85,0:10:46.62,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Instructing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.35,0:10:49.25,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,On how to catch mahi-mahi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:52.21,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's my job to catch the first one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:11:00.05,Tsuritama_Main,NATUSKI,0000,0000,0000,,Once you get one, the rest \Nof them will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:05.75,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Then all the customers will \Nbe able to catch one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.46,0:11:09.25,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.25,0:11:12.17,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, those glasses are weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:13.86,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,These are polarized glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.24,0:11:17.81,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,With them, I can see the \Nfish under the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:21.49,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Those sound great! Let me use them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:22.20,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.76,0:11:25.86,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,If one of the customers catches one,\Nget the net out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.86,0:11:28.45,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you do when you \Ncatch something big?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:31.77,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Perpendicular.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:35.30,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If you pull \Nparallel, it'll break.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.94,0:11:37.55,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.84,0:11:43.55,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Got one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.96,0:11:51.76,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,It's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.76,0:11:53.18,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:11:56.94,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:02.19,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER A,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, the net!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.79,0:12:04.30,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:06.08,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.53,0:12:11.44,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:12.31,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.15,0:12:25.39,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's so heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.74,0:12:29.02,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.82,0:12:33.29,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.29,0:12:35.66,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,S-So...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.66,0:12:37.31,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.79,0:12:39.61,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who screwed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:40.65,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you making that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:41.46,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.47,0:12:47.19,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.27,0:12:49.91,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.64,0:12:54.42,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you get the next one, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.93,0:12:57.53,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But look at this guy's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.53,0:12:59.42,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, a stone fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.10,0:13:01.05,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Stone fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:05.32,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stone fish. Stone fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:07.42,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, you're a stone fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.57,0:13:13.51,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That was an old one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.28,0:13:15.56,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.17,0:13:19.45,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:25.60,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Fish, fish, fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:27.97,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Fish, fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.97,0:13:29.24,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.79,0:13:31.73,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,surprisingly into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.74,0:13:40.30,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Good job on your first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:41.92,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:41.92,Tsuritama_Overlap,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.28,0:13:45.98,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's time for the paychecks \Nyou've been waiting for!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:49.39,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:50.48,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.55,0:13:58.23,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.23,0:14:00.61,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have money, \Nyou can't buy a pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:08.32,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Yuki.\NIt was just the first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.57,0:14:10.59,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.59,0:14:12.44,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Just take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:41.86,Tsuritama_Flashback,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.30,0:14:44.57,Tsuritama_Flashback,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.99,0:15:02.71,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:04.11,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But Yuki's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:07.73,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haru, why didn't he come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.73,0:15:10.97,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki told me to go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:13.04,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it time to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.74,0:15:15.59,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're here again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.59,0:15:18.27,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki's still not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:20.02,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:23.81,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:26.15,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he could \Ncome after embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:27.82,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,himself in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.82,0:15:30.11,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who doesn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:31.96,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki will be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:33.99,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't let something \Nlike that get him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.84,0:15:36.13,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.07,0:15:39.60,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have any friends, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.06,0:15:43.75,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:52.59,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.21,0:15:55.42,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You were fixing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:56.99,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.65,0:16:00.60,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.42,0:16:07.65,Tsuritama_Main,NATUSKI,0000,0000,0000,,Mahi-mahi gather in currents \Nwith driftwood and jetsam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.41,0:16:10.78,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for those areas when you cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:17.18,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Then bait them to you by jerking \Nyour lure back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.57,0:16:22.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Got one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.81,0:16:27.77,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've got him,\Nraise your pole and reel in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.77,0:16:29.35,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If tries to run, wait him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.35,0:16:31.00,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,When he stops, reel him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.00,0:16:33.42,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Keep doing that and wait for \Nhim to tire himself out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.79,0:16:34.71,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:37.23,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:38.92,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:42.95,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki's so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.80,0:16:47.39,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to fish, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:51.84,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:54.74,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,You're standing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:57.14,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.59,0:17:02.23,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER A,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, could I get a net?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.23,0:17:03.12,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.16,0:17:06.27,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, perpendicular!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:12.31,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Perpendicular, perpendicular,\N perpendicular!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.23,0:17:14.30,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.83,0:17:16.67,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:19.37,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.55,0:17:29.65,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.00,0:17:32.10,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you suddenly \Nable to stand today?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.10,0:17:33.82,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:35.70,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just watching Natsuki \Ncatch a mahi-mahi,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:36.86,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and before I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:38.50,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.50,0:17:41.32,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that, Keito?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.32,0:17:43.58,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,What? Yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.58,0:17:45.29,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.29,0:17:47.62,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,She says you were probably able
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:49.63,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,to stand because you love fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.59,0:17:56.61,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I see you smiling, Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.61,0:17:58.35,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just eat your food!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:04.82,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Drinks, drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.82,0:18:07.07,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Drinks, drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:08.03,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.95,0:18:12.32,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.32,0:18:13.79,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:14.86,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:20.45,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, I can see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:22.34,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Fish, fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.67,0:18:29.08,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can see them! There's tons of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:32.52,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Mahi-mahi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.64,0:18:38.68,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:42.43,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:44.67,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you cast too far, \Nyou can always reel it in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.67,0:18:45.60,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.57,0:18:47.63,Tsuritama_Main,CUSTOMER F,0000,0000,0000,,Is that kid okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.63,0:18:48.90,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:51.00,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Yuki? Fun, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.29,0:18:53.85,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.85,0:18:55.81,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,The mahi-mahi are smiling, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.18,0:19:02.64,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.05,0:19:05.98,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.98,0:19:08.12,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Bait them by jerking the \Nlure back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.70,0:19:10.49,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:13.09,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Got one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.09,0:19:15.05,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Raise the pole and reel in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:17.76,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait him out when he runs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.23,0:19:20.39,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Reel him in when he stops running.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:23.18,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:29.77,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, amazing, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:32.95,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, amazing, amazing, \Namazing, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:38.07,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.37,0:19:40.98,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.98,0:19:42.53,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:44.99,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Say it louder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:49.46,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.26,0:19:53.18,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.18,0:19:54.99,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Catch as many as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.72,0:20:00.26,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.26,0:20:01.23,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.44,0:20:08.22,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:11.74,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,See? You're a man of the sea, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:15.99,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow. That hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:20.46,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Tapioca, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.90,0:20:26.12,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:28.66,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need friends now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:31.99,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.99,0:20:34.49,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Tamocchan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:35.54,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.54,0:20:36.92,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:40.13,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:43.09,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:47.81,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found something\NI was really interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:55.23,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,They're already practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.63,0:20:56.67,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:20:58.21,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The Enoshima dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.52,0:21:02.19,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I always had friends by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.62,0:21:07.15,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,And I even surprised myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.15,0:21:10.37,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:11.89,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They took it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.89,0:21:13.68,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,by how loudly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.68,0:21:17.58,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Cast away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.82,0:21:17.58,Tsuritama_Italic_Overlap,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I learned to laugh.
